“Romantic was born to make a focus on what is the relationship between artificial intelligence and artisan intelligence by observing it in a fundamental nucleus that is the training” explained the curator of the event, Clara Tosi Pamphili “we must see the cell at first, as the boys as they study, is a tool? Need? Don't you need it? Are they victims? It is also a way to make them dialogue. Not by chance we have a large table where they are all together: from the School of Sartori that is the oldest in Italy to the boys who use Chatgpt to make an embroidery. So in this first edition it is open to all even tourists”.
&nbsp;
“The Chamber of Commerce of Rome has always been a Chamber of Commerce that looks to the future, to the new generations. Meeting here the major fashion schools, culture in our territory is a very important event because you have to network and system among those that are schools of training and enterprises. In this context we try to play a role of facilitators. The fashion world is very important. Our city was the cradle of fashion, we had our historical tailors born in Rome, as well as historical tailors. And then there is the whole chain that follows the fashion world," said Michelangelo Malchionno, a member of the Chamber of Commerce that this morning cut the ribbon of the event. &nbsp;
&nbsp;
So until Sunday, April 14, the space of the Temple of Adriano opens to the city for an unpublished experience, riding between tradition and innovation, where to master it is the fashion and the boys of the Academies of Lazio that prepare to enter the world of work with a “renovated” luggage, which no longer contemplates the scissors and sketches, but also the opportunities offered by the digital.
